contentrichtext.text: '''Quendon and Rickling''' is a [[civil parish]] in the [[Uttlesford]] district of [[Essex]], [[England]]. According to the 2001 census it had a population of 514. The parish was created in the 1940s by the merger of [[Quendon]] and [[Rickling, Essex|Rickling]] parishes. <ref>[http://www.visionofbritain.org.uk/relationships.jsp?u_id=10245552 Quendon and Rickling CP Essex through time | Administrative history of Parish-level Unit: hierarchies, boundaries<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> ==References== <references/> {{coord|51.950|0.199|type:city(514)_region:GB-ESS|display=title}} [[Category:Civil parishes in Essex]] [[Category:Uttlesford]]
